    "body": "When `root_dir` is a function it can (and often will) call the provided callback function in a fast API context (e.g. in the `on_exit` handler of `vim.system`). When the callback function is executed we should ensure that it runs vim.lsp.start on the main event loop.",
    "closed_at": "2025-01-14T14:19:54Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I'm not sure we should do this, but mostly out of principle. It's not guaranteed the user will be calling the callback in from vim.system. And if executing code in a non-fast callback is a problem then this is just a point solution to a more general problem.\n\nInteresting to know what others think.",
            "created_at": "2025-01-13T18:55:02Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/31998#issuecomment-2587947758",
            "id": 2587947758,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/31998",
            "node_id": "IC_kwDOAPphoM6aQPLu",
            "performed_via_github_app": null,
