        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The alternative is to document for `root_dir` that calling the callback _might_ have to be `vim.schedule`'d, but only in some cases, and it's not obvious when (for instance it is not even documented that vim.system's `on_exit` handler runs in a fast API context, I only learned this via the error message).\r\n\r\n>I'm not sure we should do this, but mostly out of principle\r\n\r\nI'd argue the opposite. Any async function that executes a callback/continuation may call that continuation in any context, so it's our (core's) job to ensure that the callback (which makes API calls) executes on the main loop.",
